item.title: What error is this?
item.dc:creator: @Fir3_Flam3 Fir3 Flam3
item.description:
@Fir3_Flam3 wrote:

The “cannot find symbol” message means there’s something referring to something that doesn’t exist.

Instead of pSay, but txt4.

All of these “duplicate labels” mean that there are two cases with the same numbers.

You may have this, for example:

Case 400: sendMessage("You go upstairs"); break;

and another case with the same number, such as:

Case 400: sendMessage("You pick some flax"); break;

To solve this, find the other duplicate case that you don’t need.

Read full topic
